      • findAllPaths

        public void findAllPaths(boolean weighted)
        Find all shortest paths between all pairs of vertices in this Graph

        After this method is done, each vertex shall store:
        1. The total number of vertices (not including itself) that are connected to a vertex.
        2. The sum of the number of edges in the all the shortest paths from a vertex to the vertices it connects to. (Unweighted path lengths.)
        3. The sum of the weighted path lengths in the all the shortest paths from the vertex to the vertices it connects to.

        Note, if the parameter weighted is false, 2 and 3 must equal each other.

        This method also determines the path with the greatest distance. The two most distant vertices in the Graph are those with the lognest shortest path between them. The longest path is based on the number of edges in the path if weighted == false and the unweighted shortest path algorithm is being used. The longest path is based on the highest cost shortest path if weighted == true and Dykstra is used.

        if weighted == true, use dijkstra, otherwise, use unwieghted shortest path

        After this method is called the getAllPaths, getDiamter, and get longest path methods may be called.
        Parameters:
        weighted - If weighted == true use dijkstra's algorithm otherwise use the unweighted shortest path algorithm. (Ignore any weights for edges. All edge weights considered to be 1.)

        Returns:

      • findPath

        public List<String> findPath(String destName)
        Alternative to printPath that returns an List containing the path from the current start vertex to the vertex named destName. If no path exists an empty List is returned.
        pre: destName != null, containsVertex(destName) == true, the startNode has been set by calling findUnweigthedShortesPath or dijkstra.
        Parameters:
        destName - The destination vertex
        Returns:
        A list with the path from the current start vertex to the vertex with destName. start vertex will be at index 0 and destName will be at index list.size() - 1 unless there is no path from the start vertex to destName in which case an emtpy list is returned.
